    <h1>Arthur Lee and John Adams to John Julius Pringle</h1>
    
    <div class="docbody">
     <div class="opener">
      <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Passy Feb. 12. 1779</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
     </div>
     <p>We have received your Letter of Feb. 9. offering your Services to the public by going to England to negotiate an Exchange of Prisoners. We have considered this Subject and judging it necessary to send some Person upon this Business, We have determined to accept of your Proposition, and We desire you to prepare yourself for the Journey, with all convenient Dispatch. Your Instructions shall be prepared immediately.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA07d321n1" id="PJA07d321n1-ptr">1</a></p>
     <p>We are Sir your humble Servants</p>
     <div class="closer">
      <div class="signed-multiple">
    <p class="signed multiple">Arthur Lee<br/>signed only<br/>John Adams</p>
  </div>
     </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docback">
     <div class="note-source" id="PJA07d321sn1">
      <p>
       <span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ letterbook copy (Letterbook copies are normally unsigned, but any such copy is assumed to be in the hand of the person responsible for the text unless it is otherwise described.) ]">LbC</abbr></span> in William Temple Franklins hand  (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>). This letter was enclosed in the preceding letter from <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to Lee and appears before that letter in <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s Letterbook.</span>
      </p>
     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA07d321n1-ptr" id="PJA07d321n1">1</a>
      <p>This letter may be considered the last official act by Arthur Lee and <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> as members of the joint commission to the French court. Benjamin Franklins official notification of his appointment as minister plenipotentiary arrived on 12 Feb., presumably after this letter had been drafted and sent (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Diary and Autobiography of John Adams,&lt;/i&gt; ed. L. H. Butterfield and others, Cambridge, 1961; 4 vols. ]">JA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Diary and Autobiography</span></span>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-01-02-02-0009-0001-0009" class="document">2:353</a>). Franklin did not go forward with Pringles appointment, reverting instead to his plan to name Edward Bancroft as agent. But Bancroft apparently did not go to England either. According to David Hartley, to whom Franklin had written concerning a safe conduct for Bancroft, the British ministry saw no need for an American agent in England to expedite the exchange, In any event, the first shipload of American prisoners reached France on 1 April (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ I. Minis Hays, comp., &lt;i&gt;Calendar of the Papers of Benjamin Franklin in the Library of the American Philosophical Society,&lt;/i&gt; Philadelphia, 1908; 5 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Cal. Franklin Papers, A.P.S.</span></span>, <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-07-02-pb-0406">[406<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-07/ADMS-06-07-02-pb-0406.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>2:35; Catherine Prelinger, Benjamin Franklin and the American Prisoners of War in England during the American Revolution, <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;William and Mary Quarterly.&lt;/i&gt; ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">WMQ</span></span>, 3d ser., 32:275276 [April 1975]).</p>
     </div>
    </div>
